Chelsea boss, Graham Potter, has heaped praises on the club’s latest new signing, Enzo Fernandez. Fernandez recently joined Chelsea on January transfer deadline day from Benfica. Speaking ahead of Chelsea’s Premier League tie with Fulham on Friday night, Potter described the Argentina World Cup winner as a fighter. According to him, Fernandez is not afraid, adding that the midfielder has courage. “His personality is one that makes you think you have no concerns with him. He’s a fighter,” Potter said, as quoted by Chelsea’s official website. “He understands how fortunate he is. He fights for the team, he is not afraid, he’s got courage, he’s open-minded, he wants to improve.”